reviews.review_text: Another Buffalo Jem! This show rocks from note 1! FAT set list! The boys were rude this day! They were down,and yes, they were dirty! Something about Buffalo in the summer maybe? Nice SBD,(levels a little low),but so what! Fine effort from the band on down to this posting!

Grateful Dead Rich Stadium This show was Rockin! The setlist is great. It Was the first time i saw the Dead in Buffalo and it was magical. The band played with enthusiasm and the vibe was very good. Thank you for posting this quality recording.

My first show on tour!! I drove from Green Bay, Wisconsin to this show and what a great one it was!! I sold beer for a dollar a can in the lot all day and made a killing in the hot summer sun!! I met Heather earlier that day and by the time the show started, she switched tickets with my friend, so we saw the show together. 
 First set was killer long and had a Don't Ease Me In!~ Way cool for me. What can I say, they were in that groove...awesome show!!
great one good sound quality. High Time is spectacular. Last time i saw Brent in person, great venue. Crosby, Stills and Nash opened.

Great Show!! I loved every minute of this show. I've been looking for a clean copy for years because I only have it on tape, and my 2nd set was eaten by a player so it's distorted and I'm scared to play them anymore! What a beautiful day it was. The show was so hot and I remember Relix reviewing it and saying "What? Was this a New Years show?". Oh man, if I could only time travel back to this day....
